      "title": "Stable vs Unstable Sort",
      "type": "diagram",
      "description": "What stability means",
      "content": {
        "diagram": [
          "STABILITY: Equal elements maintain relative order",
          "",
          "Original: [(A,1), (B,2), (C,1), (D,3)]",
          "Sort by number:",
          "",
          "STABLE (Merge Sort):",
          "  [(A,1), (C,1), (B,2), (D,3)]",
          "  \u2191 A still before C (original order preserved)",
          "",
          "UNSTABLE (Quick Sort) - might give:",
          "  [(C,1), (A,1), (B,2), (D,3)]",
          "  \u2191 C now before A (order changed!)",
          "",
          "When stability matters:",
          "- Sorting by multiple keys (sort by name, then by age)",
          "- Maintaining original order for ties"
        ]
      }
